title: Dubai's billion dollar trade with Iran at risk
text:
Dubai's billion dollar trade with Iran at risk 12:50pm EDT - 01:42
U.S. President Donald Trump’s decision to pull out of the Iran nuclear deal is putting at risk Dubai’s billion dollar trade with Iran. The UAE’s exports to Iran are worth about five percent of its gross domestic product, but fears around trading may see that suffer. Reuters Andrew Torchia explains. ▲ Hide Transcript ▶ View Transcript
